# Next.js Development Rules for MCP

## Project Context
This is a Next.js 15.5.4 project with TypeScript, Tailwind CSS, and React 19.

## Development Guidelines

### File Structure
- Use `src/app/` directory structure (App Router)
- Components go in `src/components/`
- Utilities go in `src/lib/`
- Types go in `src/types/`
- Use `@/` alias for imports from src directory

### Code Standards
- Use TypeScript for all files
- Prefer functional components with hooks
- Use Tailwind CSS for styling
- Follow Next.js best practices for SSR/SSG
- Use proper TypeScript types and interfaces

### MCP Integration
- Always consider performance implications
- Use Next.js built-in optimizations (Image, Link, etc.)
- Implement proper error boundaries
- Use React Server Components when appropriate
- Optimize for Core Web Vitals

### Development Commands
- `npm run dev` - Start development server with Turbopack
- `npm run build` - Build for production with Turbopack
- `npm run lint` - Run ESLint

### AI Assistant Behavior
- Always provide complete, working code examples
- Include proper TypeScript types
- Suggest performance optimizations
- Consider accessibility (a11y) requirements
- Follow Next.js 15 and React 19 patterns